Ad Text:
ABOUT US
At Custom Fleet, we’ve been using our smarts to make the complex simple for over 40 years. It’s the driving force that continues to make us the fleet and leasing leader in Australia and New Zealand today.

When you join Custom Fleet, you’re joining a business that is Going Places. With us, what you do and who you are matter. Being part of our diverse crew means you’ll feel welcome, empowered, and have lots of fun celebrating our success (and that sure does feel good!). We are a crew of accountable go-getters on a journey of continuous improvement – we collaborate and support each other, working hard to win for our customers, for our business, and for each other. Whilst winning isn’t everything, we are proud of our success and love it when we reach the #1 spot.

ABOUT THE ROLE
We are looking for a Senior Data Engineer to join our growing team and help shape the future of our cloud-native data platform. This is a Greenfield role giving you the opportunity to design and build solutions from the ground up, influence architecture decisions and set best practices for the future.

In this role you will design and develop scalable ETL/ELT pipelines in Azure ensuring data is reliable, secure and ready to power insights across the business. You will collaborate with BI Developers, Analysts and stakeholders to deliver high-quality solutions that drive smarter decisions and better outcomes for our customers.

Essential Duties

Design and build scalable ETL/ELT pipelines to ingest, transform and load data into our Azure cloud data warehouse.

Develop and maintain data engineering solutions using Azure and selected cloud-based platforms and tools.

Collaborate with BI Developers, Analysts and Business Stakeholders to understand data requirements and deliver reliable solutions.

Implement data quality checks, monitoring and governance practices across pipelines.

Work with cross-functional teams (Architecture, Infrastructure, Security) to ensure alignment with enterprise standards.

Participate in all stages of the data engineering lifecycle: design, development, testing, deployment and documentation.

Other Duties

Shape and evolve the architecture of our cloud data platform, ensuring it scales with business growth.

Contribute to the development of best practices and reusable frameworks for data ingestion and transformation.

ABOUT YOU

Essential

Proven experience in cloud-based ETL/ELT development, ideally in Azure.

Strong proficiency in Python for data engineering tasks.

Hands-on experience with Databricks and Spark.

Solid understanding of data warehousing principles and best-practice modelling.

Ability to work independently and manage complexity in a dynamic environment.

Strong problem-solving skills and attention to detail.

Other

Experience with CI/CD pipelines.

Exposure to other cloud platforms and a range of data ingestion tools.

Familiarity with data governance and security frameworks.

Education & Experience

Essential

Minimum 5 years of experience in data engineering or related fields.

Tertiary qualification in Computer Science, Data Engineering or a related discipline.

Other

Experience with Databricks, Python, Azure Data Factory, and SQL Server is highly desirable.

Experience ingesting real-time data (telemetry data) would be a bonus.

FOR YOU

We offer industry leading 'Custom Perks' including:

Annual performance bonus 

Take 5 program - potential to earn an extra week of annual leave

Gender-neutral Parental Leave - 12 weeks paid entitlement

Collaborative Hybrid work environment – 3 days in office

Company funded social events

Dress for your day policy 

Employee discounts

Intersection – our Diversity Network

Cultural Leave swap

Ongoing investment in your growth including access to our digital learning platform - Degreed

Reward and recognition programs

Volunteer and community engagement opportunities

Wellbeing leave

HOW TO APPLY

Please submit your resume and cover letter by clicking ‘Apply Now’.

At Custom Fleet we are committed to growing a team made up of diverse people, skills, and experiences. We encourage applications from all backgrounds, communities, and industries.

OUR DIVERSE CREW

Research shows that women and people of diverse backgrounds are less likely to apply for roles if they don't meet every qualification. If after reading this, you’re not sure you tick every single criteria box, but have the passion to get behind our values, we think you should click that apply button anyway. We're passionate about building a diverse and inclusive team, and love hearing from people like you!

If you have a disability that requires support including an alternate job ad format, interview arrangements or adjustments, please let us know by emailing our recruitment team at careers@customfleet.com.au or call our Customer Service Team on 1800 812 681 - they will take your details and arrange for a return call from a member of the Talent Team.

Unlawful Conduct Commitment

Custom Fleet is dedicated to maintaining a culture of respect where there is zero-tolerance of any form of discrimination, harassment, and victimisation. We are committed to eliminating unlawful conduct in the workplace and uphold the highest standards of ethical behaviour and compliance with applicable laws and regulations.

Our careers team and hiring leaders kindly request no unsolicited resumes or approaches from recruitment agencies. Custom Fleet is not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes.

Are you an experienced finance professional who thrives in a governance-focused environment and enjoys advising senior executives?

What's in it for you?

High visibility and influence, working directly with a Deputy Director-General on critical financial and governance matters.
Competitive hourly rate: $96.23 - $101.69 + Super
3 to 6 month contract | Potential view to Permanency | ASAP start
CBD Location | Possible flexible working arrangements
About the opportunity 
This is a key opportunity to work alongside a Deputy Director-General within a large Queensland Government department to lead effective divisional governance, performance, and resource management by delivering accurate analysis, reporting and business insights. Working closely with corporate finance, HR and program areas, the position ensures informed decision-making, governance, and coordinated delivery across diverse programs and initiatives.

Key Responsibilities

Provide high-level financial, business and HR advice to the DDG to support divisional operations, planning and governance.
Supports others to embrace and operate within legislative and policy frameworks that guide everyday practice.
Prepare clear, timely and evidence-based advice reports to inform executive decision-making.
Collaborate with divisional finance to coordinate financial reporting, budget monitoring and performance insights required by the DDG.
Develop and maintain analytical models and Power BI dashboards to support decision-making.
Undertake financial tasks such as accruals, journals, grants oversight and financial analysis when required.
Support HR matters, including workforce planning and performance management, where required.
Ensure effective coordination, communication and workflow within the DDG's office and across the division.
Requirements:

Proven experience providing financial, analytical and business support in a Queensland Government or large public sector environment.
Demonstrated strong governance capability
Skilled in financial reporting, analysis and modelling, with proficiency in Power BI.
Strong working knowledge of SAP (experience with SAP S/4HANA highly regarded).
Demonstrated ability to prepare clear, evidence-based advice and reports for senior executives.
Excellent interpersonal skills with the ability to support HR and business matters sensitively and effectively.

Company description:



Capgemini is a global business and technology transformation partner, helping organizations to accelerate their dual transition to a digital and sustainable world, while creating tangible impact for enterprises and society. It is a responsible and diverse group of 340,000 team members in more than 50 countries. With its strong over 55-year heritage, Capgemini is trusted by its clients to unlock the value of technology to address the entire breadth of their business needs. It delivers end-to-end services and solutions leveraging strengths from strategy and design to engineering, all fueled by its market leading capabilities in AI, generative AI, cloud and data, combined with its deep industry expertise and partner ecosystem.



Job description:

Your Role
Client Advisory: Provide expert guidance on process improvements and efficiencies achievable through Oracle SaaS solutions.
Stakeholder Engagement: Work closely with senior client stakeholders, process owners, and product owners to help them understand Oracle Cloud SaaS capabilities and support their cloud journey.
Delivery Leadership: Oversee support, enhancement, and implementation activities, including proposition development, solution design, and functional consulting leadership.
Operational Focus: Manage business-as-usual operations across the SaaS portfolio, with emphasis on ERP, EPM, PPM, and PRC processes.

Your Profile
Proven experience as a Lead on major Oracle SaaS transformation programs, including at least 4 full implementation cycles.
Strong understanding of Oracle SaaS applications and processes across multiple pillars (ERP, EPM, PPM, PRC), with a focus on ERP and Finance.
Experience managing large teams of functional consultants across SaaS pillars.
Awareness of Oracle's SaaS strategy and ability to articulate the benefits of SaaS deployments.
Desirable: Oracle Cloud Implementation Specialisation certification.

Classifications: APS6 & EL1
Salary: APS6: $98,314 – $121,026 + super & EL1: $126,341 – $154,000 + super

Work in a collaborative environment that values professionalism, innovation, and impact.

Conduct statistical and data analysis to inform briefings, submissions, policy papers, and reports.
Communicate findings clearly through concise written and verbal reports.
Provide accurate, timely advice to stakeholders with varying levels of data literacy.
Collaborate with partner agencies on data extraction, quality assurance, and complex analysis.
Ensure compliance with data governance standards.
Support the development of data analytics capability across the department through resources, training, and communication of findings.
For EL1 roles, you will also:

Lead strategic data initiatives and oversee project delivery.
Provide high-level advice to senior executives and influence decision-making.
Manage stakeholder relationships and mentor team members.

Manage competing priorities in a high-volume environment while maintaining quality and timeliness.
Apply judgment and initiative to deliver solutions, even with incomplete information.
Drive cultural and technological change to enhance data-driven decision-making (EL1).

Gepard Supply Chain Pty Ltd is a fast and reliable third-party logistics solutions business founded and headquartered in South Australia’s Barossa Valley. Our Burton depot, located at 15 Penner Ave, Burton, SA 5110, serves as the hub for our expanding operations Australia Chamber of Commerce. As we launch kongfumall.com, a next-generation data-driven logistics platform, we are seeking a seasoned data leader to join our team.

A sales oriented experience would be an advange.

Key Responsibilities

Strategy and Planning

Develop, direct, and implement the supply chain data management and analytics strategy in line with company objectives

Lead the design and delivery of analytical solutions to support the launch and ongoing operation of kongfumall

Data Operations and Intelligence

Manage the collection, processing, and quality assurance of supply chain data to produce actionable intelligence for operations and business development

Oversee day-to-day data operations, ensuring systems and processes meet performance and compliance standards

Team Leadership and Development

Recruit, train, and manage a small data and analytics team, including performance management and professional development

Provide leadership in liaising with internal stakeholders (operations, IT, finance) and external clients or partners

Reporting and Management

Liaise with contracts, accounts, and finance personnel to ensure financial timelines and targets are met

Qualifications and Experience

Minimum of 2 years’ recent and relevant work experience in data management or analytics within supply chain or logistics; Qualifications preferred in data science, information systems, or related field.

Salary: Competitive salary and bonus with great benefits
Ad Text:
As Head of Consumer Insurance Risk, you’ll provide strategic leadership to uplift risk maturity and embed robust frameworks across the division. You’ll influence decision-making at all levels, deliver actionable insights, and ensure compliance with regulatory obligations while fostering a high-performance culture.

What You’ll Do

Define and execute the Consumer Insurance Risk Strategy, aligning with business objectives and regulatory requirements
Lead initiatives to uplift risk capability and maturity, embedding consistent practices across the division
Provide expert advice on governance, frameworks, and risk appetite to strengthen decision-making
Deliver insights from internal and external data to inform strategic decisions and improve resilience
Partner with cross-functional teams to integrate risk insights into operational and strategic priorities
Inspire and develop risk teams, building capability through coaching and targeted development programs
Maintain regulator engagement through proactive communication, risk-based approaches and transparency
Regularly evaluating the design and operational effectiveness of internal controls to ensue they effectively mitigate risks

What You’ll Bring

Deep expertise in enterprise risk frameworks, insurance-specific risks, and regulatory obligations
Proven ability to set and execute risk strategies and influence senior leaders
Strong analytical skills to interpret data trends and deliver actionable insights
Experience engaging with regulators and managing governance and compliance requirements

What You’ll Enjoy

Access our award-winning Shine platform – your central hub for exclusive perks, wellbeing support, career development, and recognition. Shine has been recognised for excellence in employee experience, making it easier than ever to access what matters most to you.

Hybrid working, flexible leave, 20 weeks paid parental leave, and up to 5 days paid flexible leave annually
Paid study support, career breaks, on-the-job learning, and a $1,000 referral bonus for eligible employees
Free wellbeing coaching, a dedicated Employee Council, and confidential EAP access
Discounts at 400+ retailers, insurance savings, gym memberships, and reduced super fees
Paid volunteer leave, donation matching, and unlimited emergency response leave
Performance-based bonuses and Suncorp shares for eligible employees
Diversity is celebrated through employee resource groups and inclusive policies for all families

Explore our full benefits: www.suncorpgroup.com.au/careers/benefits

At Suncorp we believe we are our best when our workforce is as diverse, talented and passionate as the communities in which we live and operate, and where our people feel included, valued and connected. We are passionate about inspiring our people by creating a diverse, accessible, and inclusive culture, offering flexible work, career development and internal mobility, and building connected relationships amongst our team members and with our customers.

If you require any support and adjustments to participate equitably in our recruitment process or in the workplace, we encourage you to contact liam.saif@suncorp.com.au for a confidential conversation. To apply for this opportunity, please submit your application directly via the link provided.

Salary: Competitive salary and bonus with great benefits

Are you a data science expert passionate about AI innovation and stakeholder influence? We’re seeking a Staff Data Scientist to drive cutting-edge AI advancements while working closely with executives and non-technical stakeholders to shape AI adoption and impact.
This role is ideal for someone who thrives at the intersection of technical excellence and business strategy, ensuring AI solutions deliver real value across the organisation.

About the Role
As a Lead or Principal Data Scientist, you will play a crucial role in developing and deploying machine learning models, optimising AI performance, and influencing key business decisions. Your expertise in NLP, LLMs, and MLOps will drive innovation, while your ability to communicate complex AI concepts to executives will ensure AI initiatives align with business objectives.
This is a high-visibility role where you’ll work across teams, bridging the gap between technical execution and business strategy—helping senior stakeholders understand the power of AI and how to apply it effectively.

Key Responsibilities
AI Strategy & Business Alignment – Work closely with executives and business leaders to integrate AI-driven solutions into company strategy.
Technical Leadership – Design, develop, and optimise machine learning models, with a focus on NLP and large-scale AI applications.
Executive Stakeholder Influence – Translate complex AI concepts into clear, actionable insights for non-technical leaders.
MLOps & AI Engineering – Implement best practices for model deployment, monitoring, and performance optimisation at scale.
Data-Driven Decision Making – Drive high-impact AI initiatives by leveraging advanced analytics on structured and unstructured data.
Research & Innovation – Stay ahead of AI trends, applying cutting-edge techniques to enhance business performance and operational efficiency.
What You’ll Bring
8+ years of experience (Staff Level) in data science, AI, and machine learning, with strong expertise in NLP and LLMs.
A track record of engaging with C-suite and senior business stakeholders, influencing AI strategy and execution.
Expert-level Python and SQL skills, with deep experience in building and deploying machine learning models at scale.
Hands-on experience with MLOps best practices, cloud-based AI solutions, and large-scale data processing.
A strategic mindset, with the ability to translate AI advancements into business impact.
Exceptional communication and influencing skills, able to simplify complex concepts for non-technical audiences.
What’s in It for You?
Work at the forefront of AI innovation, shaping strategy at a high-growth tech company.
Partner directly with executives and business leaders to drive enterprise-wide AI transformation.
Join a team that values curiosity, technical excellence, and real-world AI applications.
Hybrid work model (Sydney-based, 2-3 days in-office).
If you’re a highly experienced AI professional who can influence at an executive level while delivering cutting-edge AI solutions, we’d love to hear from you. Apply now!

Are you a data science expert passionate about AI innovation and stakeholder influence? We’re seeking a Senior Data Scientist to drive cutting-edge AI advancements while working closely with executives and non-technical stakeholders to shape AI adoption and impact.
This role is ideal for someone who thrives at the intersection of technical excellence and business strategy, ensuring AI solutions deliver real value across the organisation.

About the Role
Join a rapidly growing AI-driven organisation at the forefront of innovation in LLMs, NLP, and Generative AI. This role is ideal for a hands-on data scientist who thrives in building scalable AI solutions, experimenting with state-of-the-art models, and driving real-world impact through applied research and engineering excellence. You’ll work across multi-cloud environments, collaborate with technical and business stakeholders, and help shape the next generation of intelligent systems.
Key Responsibilities
LLM & NLP Development – Design, fine-tune, and deploy advanced large language models (PEFT, LoRA, PPO) to solve complex business challenges.
GenAI & RAG Engineering – Build and optimise retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) pipelines, embedding models, and agentic AI architectures.
MLOps & Deployment – Implement scalable ML workflows with CI/CD, monitoring, benchmarking, and automation best practices across AWS, GCP, or Azure.
Collaboration & Influence – Work closely with cross-functional teams to translate AI research into production-ready solutions that deliver measurable outcomes.
Continuous Research – Stay ahead of emerging trends in LLMs, transformers, reinforcement learning, and generative architectures.
What You’ll Bring
4–8 years of hands-on experience in data science, AI, or machine learning, with deep knowledge of NLP and LLM applications.
Strong proficiency in Python, PyTorch, and SQL, plus experience with frameworks such as LangChain, Hugging Face, or LlamaIndex.
Practical experience building RAG pipelines, integrating vector databases (Pinecone, Weaviate, FAISS), and deploying solutions through Databricks, SageMaker, or Vertex AI.
Understanding of MLOps, monitoring, and feature store design, ensuring performance and reliability at scale.
Curiosity and drive to experiment with new architectures, delivering meaningful improvements to model capability and business value.
What’s in It for You
Contribute to cutting-edge AI initiatives in a fast-paced, high-impact environment.
Collaborate with talented engineers, researchers, and product leaders who share a passion for innovation.
Access modern tech stacks, flexible hybrid working, and opportunities to shape enterprise-level GenAI adoption.
Be part of a team that values curiosity, technical mastery, and solving real-world problems with AI.

If you’re a highly experienced AI professional who can influence at an executive level while delivering cutting-edge AI solutions, we’d love to hear from you. Apply now!

This is an excellent opportunity for an energetic, dynamic Senior Commercial Analyst to join a successful, global construction group.

Reporting into the CFO you'll act as a business partner to operational stakeholders, providing commercial, financial & analytical support, to help drive decisions & business performance.

Your analytical scope will encompass areas such as category sales, discounting, gross margins, pre & post promotional analysis and wages. You'll create financial models in order to provide meaningful insights into business performance issues, challenging decisions where necessary.

You'll also prepare and distribute weekly & monthly reports, with associated commentary, for use by the business. And will hold regular meetings with Category Managers and the Commercial Director, to review monthly sales, margin results etc.

Additionally, you'll play a key role in business planning for new stores, budgeting, forecasting and other ad hoc analysis when required.

You are an experienced Financial or Commercial Analyst - who will be ready to step into a Commercial Manager role in the next 1-2 years. Circa 5 years experience in Commercial Finance role/s would be ideal.

You'll have proven analytical skills, combined with a background in business partnering. You will also have advanced Excel / modelling skills, whilst experience using a BI tool and working with large data sets.

For more information, please contact Schenuk Wijesekera on 02 9775 5916. Or to apply, hit the "apply" button.

We’re looking for a talented and commercially minded Senior Pricing Analyst to join our growing team and play a key role in shaping pricing, portfolio performance and strategic growth across our home and motor insurance products. This role blends actuarial rigour, data analytics, and cross-functional collaboration to drive confident decisions that enhance customer value, support underwriting partnerships, and strengthen Honey’s product portfolio.

Who We Are

We're shaking up the home insurance industry! As a disruptor in the insurance space, we combine smart technology with exceptional service to create home insurance that's simpler, faster, and more customer-friendly. Our innovative approach includes smart sensors that help prevent incidents before they happen, a streamlined digital experience, and genuine human support when customers need it most.

About The Role

We’re seeking a Senior Pricing Analyst with strong actuarial capability, sharp commercial thinking, and a passion for data-driven decision-making. You’ll build and maintain pricing models, analyse portfolio performance, develop predictive models, and support strategic initiatives across product development, partnerships, and regulatory matters. You’ll work closely with teams across Product, Engineering, Finance and Operations, translating complex insights into clear and actionable recommendations.

Key Responsibilities

Pricing and portfolio analysis

Build and maintain pricing models across home, and motor insurance products
Analyse loss ratios, claim rates, and customer behaviour across segments to inform pricing decisions
Support pricing negotiations with underwriting partners by supporting actuarial analysis and business cases

Data analytics and reporting

Deliver regular reporting on portfolio performance, claims trends, and customer metrics across all product lines
Conduct deep-dive analyses on emerging risks, customer cohorts, and product performance
Develop predictive models to identify risk factors and optimise customer interventions
Create dashboards and visualisations to communicate insights to stakeholders

Strategic projects

Support product development and market entry decisions with actuarial analysis
Evaluate new partnership opportunities and distribution channels
Contribute to business cases for technology investments and product enhancements
Collaborate on regulatory and compliance matters requiring actuarial input

Stakeholder engagement

Translate complex actuarial and data concepts into actionable recommendations for non-technical audiences
Build relationships across product, engineering, operations, and finance teams

What You'll Bring

Must haves

Associate (AIAA) or near-Associate level (Part II complete) with the Actuaries Institute
3-5 years of experience in general insurance (ideally across multiple product lines such as home, motor or pet)
Strong understanding of actuarial principles, loss reserving, and risk assessment
Advanced SQL for data extraction and transformation
Python or R for statistical analysis and modelling (pandas, scikit-learn, statsmodels)
Experience with data visualisation tools (Tableau, Looker, or similar)
Comfortable working with cloud data platforms
Understanding of modern data infrastructure and version control

What sets you apart

Ability to balance actuarial rigour with commercial pragmatism
Curiosity, comfort with ambiguity and able to work autonomously
Strong communication skills - you can explain technical concepts to diverse audiences
Detail-oriented but don't lose sight of the bigger picture
Interest in insurtech and how technology is reshaping insurance

Why You'll Love Honey

Competitive salary package with performance-based incentives
Opportunity to shape and lead a critical function in a high-growth company
Enviable company culture of innovation, collaboration and high performance
Hybrid work model blending office collaboration with remote flexibility
Monthly team lunches, celebrations, social events & initiatives

Our Hive Culture

At Honey, we do things differently. You'll notice this from your first interaction with our team through to your first day with us. We challenge expectations, seek better ways of working, and value innovation at every turn.

We're exceptional at what we do, and every team member brings unique talent to our hive. As an equal opportunity employer, we're committed to diversity and inclusion, it's in our DNA, not just something we talk about.

A Few Formalities

Because we're an AFSL-regulated business, this role requires background checks (including a National Police Check) and meeting "good fame and character" standards. Candidates must be Sydney-based.

Ready to lead the transformation of customer support in insurance?

Apply now and help us build something extraordinary. If you`d like to find out more, you can contact us at people@honeyinsurance.com.

No recruitment agencies, please. We've got this covered.

Senior PMO Analyst – 12 Month Contract
Location: Sydney, NSW (3 days onsite, 2 days WFH)
Rate: Up to $950/day inc super

The Opportunity
My client is embarking on a major transformation program and is seeking an experienced Senior PMO Analyst to support delivery. This is an initial 12-month contract with strong potential to extend, working in a growing PMO function.
Key Responsibilities

Provide hands-on PMO support across a complex program.
Manage and maintain program logs, including risks, issues, dependencies, and decision registers.
Prepare and deliver high-quality status and progress reports for senior stakeholders.
Support governance processes and ensure program standards are adhered to.
Work flexibly with the project team, stepping in to assist with ad-hoc tasks where needed.
About You

DATA MIGRATION SPECIALIST - SAP S4HANA UPGRADE

A major Finance Transformation Program is underway, transitioning from SAP ECC6 to SAP S/4HANA. We are seeking an experienced Data Migration Specialist to support the delivery of this upgrade by driving data analysis, mapping, modelling, cleansing, testing and migration activities across complex financial datasets.

This role will work closely with Business Analysts, finance and ICT stakeholders, and technical SME's to ensure all data is understood, transformed and migrated effectively to support the uplift to S/4HANA.

KEY RESPONSIBILITIES
Develop data migration artefacts including strategy, plan, approach, mapping specifications, test cases and data archiving considerations.
Execute data migration activities including extraction, transformation, cleansing, auditing, and reconciliation.
Conduct data profiling and remediation across in-scope datasets.
Build logical and physical data models aligned to business and finance processes.
Produce source-to-target mappings and document complex transformation rules.
Provide expert advice on data quality, business impacts, risk, scope and requirements.
Support User Acceptance Testing and work within established project methodologies.
Collaborate with a wide range of stakeholders across the program.
ABOUT YOU
Demonstrated experience delivering data migration for large SAP finance projects.
Strong background in SAP ECC6 and an understanding of S/4HANA capabilities (FI/CO, Universal Journal, Fiori).
Advanced analytical, problem solving and modelling skills.
Ability to write complex SQL/scripts and perform data extraction and transformation.
Strong communication skills with the ability to build relationships across technical and business teams.
Experience working under pressure with tight timeframes and changing priorities.

If you have the experience and capability to support a major SAP S/4HANA transformation, we would love to hear from you.
